"\n"
"| `id`\n"
"| The ID of the marshaller\n"
"| No\n"
"\n"
"| `contextPath`\n"
"| The JAXB Context path\n"
"| No\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:428
#, no-wrap
msgid "JiBX"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:435
msgid ""
"The JiBX framework offers a solution similar to that which Hibernate "
"provides for ORM: A binding definition defines the rules for how your Java "
"objects are converted to or from XML. After preparing the binding and "
"compiling the classes, a JiBX binding compiler enhances the class files and "
"adds code to handle converting instances of the classes from or to XML."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:439
msgid ""
"For more information on JiBX, see the http://jibx.sourceforge.net/[JiBX web "
"site]. The Spring integration classes reside in the "
"`org.springframework.oxm.jibx` package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:441
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using `JibxMarshaller`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:447
msgid ""
"The `JibxMarshaller` class implements both the `Marshaller` and "
"`Unmarshaller` interface. To operate, it requires the name of the class to "
"marshal in, which you can set using the `targetClass` property. Optionally, "
"you can set the binding name by setting the `bindingName` property. In the "
"following example, we bind the `Flights` class:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:456
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<beans>\n"
"\t\t<bean id=\"jibxFlightsMarshaller\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.oxm.jibx.JibxMarshaller\">\n"
"\t\t\t<property "
"name=\"targetClass\">org.springframework.oxm.jibx.Flights</property>\n"
"\t\t</bean>\n"
"\t\t...\n"
"\t</beans>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:461
msgid ""
"A `JibxMarshaller` is configured for a single class. If you want to marshal "
"multiple classes, you have to configure multiple `JibxMarshaller` instances "
"with different `targetClass` property values."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:467
msgid ""
"The `jibx-marshaller` tag configures a "
"`org.springframework.oxm.jibx.JibxMarshaller`, as the following example "
"shows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:471
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<oxm:jibx-marshaller id=\"marshaller\" "
"target-class=\"org.springframework.ws.samples.airline.schema.Flight\"/>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:489
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Attribute| Description| Required\n"
"\n"
"| `id`\n"
"| The ID of the marshaller\n"
"| No\n"
"\n"
"| `target-class`\n"
"| The target class for this marshaller\n"
"| Yes\n"
"\n"
"| `bindingName`\n"
"| The binding name used by this marshaller\n"
"| No\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:493
#, no-wrap
msgid "XStream"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:497
msgid ""
"XStream is a simple library to serialize objects to XML and back again. It "
"does not require any mapping and generates clean XML."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:501
msgid ""
"For more information on XStream, see the https://x-stream.github.io/[XStream "
"web site]. The Spring integration classes reside in the "
"`org.springframework.oxm.xstream` package."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:503
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using `XStreamMarshaller`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:508
msgid ""
"The `XStreamMarshaller` does not require any configuration and can be "
"configured in an application context directly. To further customize the XML, "
"you can set an alias map, which consists of string aliases mapped to "
"classes, as the following example shows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:521
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<beans>\n"
"\t\t<bean id=\"xstreamMarshaller\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.oxm.xstream.XStreamMarshaller\">\n"
"\t\t\t<property name=\"aliases\">\n"
"\t\t\t\t<props>\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t<prop "
"key=\"Flight\">org.springframework.oxm.xstream.Flight</prop>\n"
"\t\t\t\t</props>\n"
"\t\t\t</property>\n"
"\t\t</bean>\n"
"\t\t...\n"
"\t</beans>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:529
msgid ""
"By default, XStream lets arbitrary classes be unmarshalled, which can lead "
"to unsafe Java serialization effects. As such, we do not recommend using the "
"`XStreamMarshaller` to unmarshal XML from external sources (that is, the "
"Web), as this can result in security vulnerabilities."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:532
msgid ""
"If you choose to use the `XStreamMarshaller` to unmarshal XML from an "
"external source, set the `supportedClasses` property on the "
"`XStreamMarshaller`, as the following example shows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:539
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\t<bean id=\"xstreamMarshaller\" "
"class=\"org.springframework.oxm.xstream.XStreamMarshaller\">\n"
"\t\t<property name=\"supportedClasses\" "
"value=\"org.springframework.oxm.xstream.Flight\"/>\n"
"\t\t...\n"
"\t</bean>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:542
msgid ""
"Doing so ensures that only the registered classes are eligible for "
"unmarshalling."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:550
msgid ""
"Additionally, you can register "
"{spring-framework-api}/oxm/xstream/XStreamMarshaller.html#setConverters(com.thoughtworks.xstream.converters.ConverterMatcher...)[custom "
"converters] to make sure that only your supported classes can be "
"unmarshalled. You might want to add a `CatchAllConverter` as the last "
"converter in the list, in addition to converters that explicitly support the "
"domain classes that should be supported.  As a result, default XStream "
"converters with lower priorities and possible security vulnerabilities do "
"not get invoked."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/origin/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/data-access/oxm.adoc:554
msgid ""
"Note that XStream is an XML serialization library, not a data binding "
"library.  Therefore, it has limited namespace support. As a result, it is "
"rather unsuitable for usage within Web Services."
msgstr ""
